      • getGlobalBuildingIfExists

        public Building getGlobalBuildingIfExists()
        This logic is based on airport.js's loadMap() which is the code responsible for picking the default building/structure and default floor of that building/structure that the user is placed on when the map first loads. That selection is not done by the LocusMaps Android SDK, to be clear it's done by the LocusMaps JavaScript Core SDK. Ideally, there should be one place for this piece of logic. It is replicated here though in case the LocusMaps Android SDK needs to know which building/structure + floor was chosen by default.

        This method determines if there is a global building and returns it.

        Specified by:
        getGlobalBuildingIfExists in interface Venue
        Returns:
        the building designated as global if it exists, null otherwise

      • getFirstNonGlobalBuilding

        public Building getFirstNonGlobalBuilding()
        This logic is based on airport.js's loadMap() which is the code responsible for picking the default building/structure and default floor of that building/structure that the user is placed on when the map first loads. That selection is not done by the LocusMaps Android SDK, to be clear it's done by the LocusMaps JavaScript Core SDK. Ideally, there should be one place for this piece of logic. It is replicated here though in case the LocusMaps Android SDK needs to know which building/structure + floor was chosen by default.

        Note that the logic venue.getDefaultFloors().get(0).getId() will most likely give you the wrong thing. For example, at wfs, it gives you wfs-global-4 whereas getFirstNonGlobalBuildingDefaultFloorId() gives you wfs-build-2.

        See also the javadoc comments of this super class.

        One way that this code differs from airport.js's loadMap() is that it ignores any non-global buildings which have shouldDisplay=false, for example at venue hkg. Keywords: JavaScript Core SDK, airport.js, loadMap()

        Specified by:
        getFirstNonGlobalBuilding in interface Venue
        Returns:
        first non-global Building or null if none found

      • getEnableGrab

        public boolean getEnableGrab()
        Description copied from interface: Venue
        Returns whether or not Grab support should be overridden for this venue. In other words, it's possible for the Grab organization to provide service for the venue but for LocusLabs customers to prevent it from appearing on the user interface. If enableGrab is true, then Grab will be supported as long as all other conditions are met such as the Grab framework is detected and the Grab organization supports Grab at the venue. If enableGrab is false, then Grab will not be supported, not matter what. Defaults to true if no value is available.
        Specified by:
        getEnableGrab in interface Venue
        Returns:
        whether Grab support should be overridden

      • getFirstNonGlobalBuildingDefaultFloorId

        public java.lang.String getFirstNonGlobalBuildingDefaultFloorId()

        See also the javadoc comments of this super class.

      • getNavigationSegments

        public void getNavigationSegments(MapView mapView,
                                  Position startPosition,
                                  Position endPosition,
                                  Venue.OnGetNavigationSegmentsListener listener,
                                  Venue.OnGetNavigationSegmentsFailureListener failureListener)
        Description copied from interface: Venue
        Provided a proper starting and ending position, asynchronously get the NavigationEvent Summary for two positions which details all information relevant to a navigation.

        The returned NavigationSummary is comprised of the following properties:
        • String startingName
        • String endingName
        • Double eta
        • List of NavigationSegment navigationSegments
        Specified by:
        getNavigationSegments in interface Venue
        startPosition - The first Position on a navigation's route from which a list of navigation steps and on-route landmarks can be derived.
        endPosition - The last Position on a navigation's route from which a list of navigation steps and on-route landmarks can be derived.
        listener - listener when the estimate has been computed
        failureListener - called if any errors occur trying to compute a route
        See Also:
        "NavigationEvent", "LocusLabs JavaScript SDK - locuslabs.maps.NavigationSummaryBox"
